<p>Unfortunately, I did not observe these or similar events when launching =
=E2=80=98native=E2=80=99 executables. As an alternative to relying on just =
the logs, the <code class=3D"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">os_trace=
_relay</code> Lockdown Service does allow you to query the current list of =
running processes. This is done with pyMobileDevice3 by doing:</p>
<div class=3D"language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class=3D"highlight"><=
pre class=3D"highlight"><code><span class=3D"c1"># lockdown =3D create_usin=
g_tcp(...)
</span><span class=3D"n">trace_service</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> =
<span class=3D"n">OsTraceService</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span clas=
s=3D"n">lockdown</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
